  "prompt": "Why is Chicago called the \"City of Broad Shoulders\"?",
  "response": "Chicago is nicknamed the \"City of Broad Shoulders\" due to a poem written by Carl Sandburg in 1914 titled \"Chicago.\" In the poem, Sandburg describes the city as a robust, industrial powerhouse, emphasizing its strength and resilience. The line that specifically references this nickname is, \"Come and show me another city with lifted head singing so proud to be alive and coarse and strong and cunning.\" The \"broad shoulders\" symbolize Chicago's ability to carry heavy economic and industrial burdens, reflecting its role as a major hub for commerce, transportation, and manufacturing during the early 20th century.",
